ecsAgentManagementEntry.description: A source address address and privileges of a particular management station.

ecsAgentManagementAccess.name: ecsAgentManagementAccess
ecsAgentManagementAccess.description: Setting this object to the value invalid(1) invalidates the corresponding entry in the ecsAgentManagementTable. That is, it effectively disassociates the address identified with the entry by removing the entry from the table.

ecsAgentManAccessLevel.name: ecsAgentManAccessLevel
ecsAgentManAccessLevel.description: The level of aceess attributed to tthis entry in the table.

A new link will always be configured with the main link being the active link. If the link status cannot be determined, the value unknown(1) is returned.

configurationChanged.description: The LinkBuilder ECS configuartion has changed. Either a card has been added or removed, a port disabled or enabled from the front panel or a AUI port has been selected/deselected.

resilientLinkTrap.name: resilientLinkTrap

rateTrap.name: rateTrap
rateTrap.description: A Guage threshold has been exceeded. The slot and port number are given by the vakues if ecsInfoSlotIndex and ecsInfoPortIndex and the guage that has been exceeded is given by the value of ecsPortErrorState.

stationlocateTrap.name: stationlocateTrap
stationlocateTrap.description: The Station Locate databse has either changed or has become full. The particular condition is shown by the value of ecsRLCSLDataBAseStatus returned.

secureRLCTrap.name: secureRLCTrap
secureRLCTrap.description: There has been access to the security menus from the front panel menus. The value of ecsAgentSecureManagementStatus reports whether the trap was generated beacuse the security menus were entered, the secure password was violated or the security configuration has been changed.

secureRLCportTrap.name: secureRLCportTrap
secureRLCportTrap.description: A secure port has either detected an authorised port and taken appropriate action or has learnt an authorised station on the slot and port indicated.
